Took us a while to flag them down again to get our check at the end of the night. Seemed like they were uninterested in serving us because we were only there for drinks and not dinner.. even though most of the tables in the restaurant were empty. Someone at our table tried the El Topo cocktail and had to down a whole glass of water after one sip because it was so spicy. The ambiance is great, but I'm not sure what happened this time around.

Food was great, nothing to complain about it. However, very disappointed about the service. First of all we ordered some fries along with our meal that we ordered at the same time. The rest of the meal arrived, except the fries. After waiting for a while and seeing that people arriving later than us were already served some fries we asked to the waiter about the situation. Then with an indifferent and very patronising tone of voice he said that we could start the meal without the fries. At that moment we were in shock. Obviously the issue is not the fries, cause after all, the food looked delicious. The issue was how condescending the waiter was towards us, which made us already disappointed about our meal. Then he brought the fries without saying a single word, just leaving them on the table. He didn’t check back on us at all or apologised at any point. When we finished, another member of staff (very polite, he looked like the supervisor/manager) dropped us the bill. After paying, the previous waiter came to the table (with the same patronising attitude) and told us that the gratuity/tip was not included, implied we should pay for it. As a person who works in hospitality in a restaurant myself, I would never dare to speak to a customer like the way he did and not even apologise for the service AND also expect to get a tip. I’m afraid I don’t feel that’s fair on me as a customer. Hope this review is taken into account.
